One of the leaders of recent years, FC Atalanta from Bergamo may go under the control of American investors.  According to Nicolo Schira, US’s Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. can buy 80% percent of the shares of Atalanta. The expected price of a deal is near 350 million euros, the Percassi family will save a minority share and will still be ruling Atalanta within the transfer period. Atalanta will become the 7th club purchased by the US investors in Serie A. As Betonmobile.ru corresponds, six other clubs from the elite of Italian football have been taken over earlier: AC Milan (Elliott Management Corporation), AS Roma (Dan Friedkin), ASF Fiorentina (executive Rocco B. Comisso). Genoa’s (777 Partners), Spezia’s (Robert Platek) and Venezia’s (VFC Newco 2020 LLC) owners also come from USA. American capital is also attracted to a number of teams from the lower leagues of Italy. Oshodi Solicits Support For Development Of Judo Team GB Loses Olympic 4×100m Silver Medal To Doping Atalanta is one of the most entertaining and stables clubs in Italy for the last couple of seasons. The Bergamasque haven’t won serious trophies of professional level since 1963, but soon after the arrival of Gian Piero Gasperini, the team always is one of the representatives of Italy in European competitions. For example. In the last campaign, Atalanta barely lost to Real Madrid in the quarterfinals of the Champions League. This season Atalanta dropped out of the UCL due to a loss in the last match to Villarreal, but soon became one of the main favourites to win the Europa League. Traditionally, the Goddess is one of the pretenders to claim the fourth spot to qualify for the next Champions League campaign, which the club may be trying to win under new owners.